Description: Rim and body sherd of East Greek (North Ionian) pottery rosette bowl; interior glazed with added red band lined in white; exterior: top of rim glazed; set of verticals with part of a rosette to left and streaky band below; inscription cut on lower wall outside.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis), temenos (said to be)
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.842)
